dcterms:creator: Leela Zero Chess Development Community
dcterms:description: Leela Chess Zero is an open source, community initiative for training superhuman chess models through self-play, in the same style as AlphaZero. The project generates training data by self-play through community-wide distributed computing.
dcterms:title: Leela Chess Zero

dcterms:creator: Lichess
dcterms:description: The Lichess Puzzle Database contains chess positions and the first move that gives a significant advantage for the player to move, ensuring that each position has a single candidate move.
dcterms:title: Lichess Puzzle Database

dcterms:creator: Patrik Hammersborg
dcterms:description: Concept functions used for concept detection in chess models, adapted for use in explainable AI approaches for deep reinforcement learning agents.
